  <!-- FAQ Content -->
  <main class="container">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FQA)</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>1. What is this platform about?</h3>
      <p>This platform connects food donors with people in need by minimizing food wastage and maximizing food distribution efficiency.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>2. How can I register as a donor?</h3>
      <p>Click on the "Donar" menu link, fill out your details, and submit the registration form. Once approved, you can start donating food.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>3. How can I request food?</h3>
      <p>Go to the "Reciver" section, register yourself, and browse available food listings. Click request on any item you need.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>4. Is there any cost to use this service?</h3>
      <p>No, this is a completely free platform aimed at helping reduce food waste and hunger in communities.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>5. Can I cancel a request after placing it?</h3>
      <p>Yes, you can cancel your request by logging into your account and clicking the cancel button beside the requested item.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>6. How is food quality ensured?</h3>
      <p>All donors are requested to provide only hygienic and safe-to-eat food. The platform regularly reviews donor activities to maintain trust and safety.</p>
    </div>
  </main>

